## P21 — Bull / Bear / Noise-vs-Structural axis grid *(promotion of ASML custom CSS)*

**Detect.** H2 matches `/sell[- ]side disagreement|disagreement axes|the question(s)? sell[- ]side is having/i` AND inside the section, two-or-more H3s each followed by a structured block where the **first** non-empty paragraph after the H3 is bolded and contains `the question` (case-insensitive), AND the subsequent body contains bolded labels matching `Bull:`, `Bear:`, and `Noise vs.? structural:` (in any order). Detection is per-axis-H3: each H3 that meets the per-axis conditions becomes a card; H3s in the same section that don't meet the conditions fall through to prose.

**Markdown shape.** Matches both GOOG.md (`### (i) Interface disruption` … `**The question:** …` … `- **Bull:** …` `- **Bear:** …` `- **Noise vs. structural:** …`) and ASML.md (`### 1. Capex-cycle trough timing` etc.) as-written. Zero markdown changes.

**HTML.** Three regions: a question banner (full-width header), then a two-column Bull/Bear pair, then a full-width NVS panel beneath. This is the same shape ASML.html currently produces:

