## P22 — Layer-tagged failure-mode cards *(promotion of ASML custom CSS)*

**Detect.** H2 matches `/failure modes?|thesis[- ]breaking|structural failure/i` AND the body's primary content is a bullet list (allowing optional intro `<p>` above) where **at least 50% of the bullets** end with a bracketed `[xxx layer]` tag (case-insensitive, allowing `[FX layer]`, `[regulatory layer]`, `[accounting layer]`, etc.). The 50% threshold accommodates partial-migration playbooks; if no bullets have tags, fall through to prose. The renderer extracts the tag from each bullet and the bullet body before it, plus the leading `**bold lead-in:**` if present.

**Markdown shape.** Matches GOOG.md lines 148–158 and ASML.md lines 162–172 as-written (each bullet ends with `[interface layer]`, `[demand layer]`, etc.). Zero markdown changes.

**Layer palette (fixed across all playbooks).** The renderer maps each layer literal to a token pair; the table below is the authoritative mapping and must be reproduced verbatim in the catalogue entry:

| Layer literal | Class | Background token | Foreground token |
|---|---|---|---|
| `interface` | `p-fm-tag-interface` | `--accent-soft` | `--accent` |
| `monetisation` / `monetization` | `p-fm-tag-monetisation` | `--info-soft` | `--info` |
| `cost` | `p-fm-tag-cost` | `--warn-soft` | `--warn` |
| `ecosystem` | `p-fm-tag-ecosystem` | `--info-soft` | `--info` |
| `demand` | `p-fm-tag-demand` | `--danger-soft` | `--danger` |
| `regulatory` | `p-fm-tag-regulatory` | `--warn-soft` | `--warn` |
| `technology` | `p-fm-tag-technology` | `--accent-soft` | `--accent` |
| `accounting` | `p-fm-tag-accounting` | `--rule-soft` | `--muted` |
| `FX` | `p-fm-tag-fx` | `--info-soft` | `--info` |

Unknown layers (a future playbook might add `[supply layer]` or `[geo layer]`) fall to a default `p-fm-tag-other` using `--rule-soft / --muted`.

